==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|[pʌnt]}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌnt|-ʌnt]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

===Etymology 1===
{{L.}} '' ponto - onis'': A [[Gaulish]] flat bottomed boat.

# {{nautical}}: A [[pontoon]]; a narrow shallow boat propelled by a pole.

===Etymology 2===
Dialect: Possibly from [[butt]].

# (sport) In soccer, rugby, American football etc. a play where the ball is kicked upfield, usually without an intended receiver, in order to gain territory.

===Etymology 3===
{{Sp.}} ''ponto'': point.

# A bet or wager.
# ''(metaphorical):'' A highly speculative investment or other commitment, a wild guess.


